      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Good Will Hunting</p>
        <p>Robin Williams, Matt Damon, Ben Affleck, Minnie Driver</p>
        <p>Directed by Gus Van Sant  R  125 minutes</p>
        <p>''I'm pumped. Let the healing begin,'' the cocky Will Hunting (Mr. Damon) says sarcastically to Sean (Mr. Williams), his new psychiatrist. Hired as a janitor at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, young Will exhibits a mathematical aptitude on the far side of Einstein. Problem is, he's also a fist fighter from South Boston whose abusive upbringing has left him fearful and closed off from his intellectual birthright. It's up to Sean, a former abused kid with a lot of the same issues, to try to undo the damage. Can both, or either, be saved?</p>
        <p>VIOLENCE There is one brawl in a playground, and Sean grabs Will by the throat in a heated moment.  SEX Will and a Harvard student (Ms. Driver) go to bed, but nothing is explicit. There is much lewd banter, and in one scene someone has just finished masturbating.  PROFANITY A good deal.</p>
        <p>For Which Children?</p>
        <p>UNDER 13 If the language isn't a problem, older children in this category will enjoy this film.  AGES 13 AND UP Mr. Damon and his character will appeal to teen-agers.</p>
        <p>PETER M. NICHOLS</p>
      </block>
